                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm probably one of the more pro-Blizzard people around.  That said, I've come to realize recently that not all of the whiners about -insert bug etc- are totally off base.
<br />

<br />
Let's start <a href="http://patchtimer.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">here</a>.  We're at over 2 months since a content patch occurred (that failed to fix many known bugs, broken quests, etc.) - content that was pretty much limited to adding one 45-50 single group instance, Maraudon.  Perhaps MC was also added, I have no clue if it was in the game before then.
<br />

<br />
Since release, we've also had hotfixes, and maintenance cycles allegedly to mitigate server problems, but included unannounced changes to class abilities (sorry, but this should <span style="font-style: italic">never</span> happen in an organization the size of Blizzard).  While the rhetoric regarding class fixes seems positive to some (depends on who you ask whether a maybe-someday soulshard bag for warlocks, a dd finishing move for druids, and the myriad of other feedback are positive), the implementation behind those fixes is sorely lacking.
<br />

<br />
In regards to PvE raids, some guilds have reported a work-around exists for the lockout bug - others are fuming about it.  Raid loot bug reports exist (my guild seems to raid FFA to prevent people not being able to roll/loot something), and raiding in general is pretty much taking place in about 4 zones.
<br />

<br />
PvP - well pretty much numbers win.  Personally, I'm happy to see a lot of Alliance activity on my server (where Horde:Alliance is about 3:2).  Anyone on a PvP server (and probably most on PvE as well) has probably experienced the "slideshow" raids that seem to occur anytime there is a guard zerg or 50-60 PCs get in close proximity.  All in all - there is no reward system, so it's something to do when not playing an alt.
<br />

<br />
The longer time drags without a content patch I begin to wonder - does Blizz really know wth they're doing?  I have high hopes for Battlegrounds (withholding judgement on PvP rewards until I see the system), but the ETA on that is unknown.
<br />

<br />
This isn't a rant, or a whine - I'm having a lot of fun in the game, and still haven't seen much of BRD/Scholo/Strat on my main yet.  I'm really starting to appreciate my druid alt (enjoying it a lot more than my priest alt).  Last weekend I started a NE hunter on Frostmane to give alliance side a try (the rumors about 2 to 4x the quests are true lol).
<br />

<br />
The longer Blizz does go without a meaningful content patch though; it makes me suspicious whether they can hold this together long term.
<br />

<br />
-edit- forgot to add, the WoW forums are down again lol !</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nokei Orhaste &lt;Retired&gt; E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10</a></span>
