                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To be honest bugs have never bothered me to much, I just assume all games will have them at least MMORPGs anyway just because of the scope of the project, and a rudementary understanding of how complicated games will be. As for content patches well, we haven't really had one yet. They launched, then had the Christmas celebration which I'm sure was planned ahead of time but I *expect* Blizzard to release content every serveral months rather then pushing it out quickly. On the same not, I expect a content patch to be exceptionally well tested, and contain many new and fun things to do that enhance my gameplay. I'm reserving my opinion until after Battlgrounds are released, just to see what the scope of these content patches will be.
<br />

<br />
As for PvP - in MMORPGs it will *never* be possible to have balanced PvP that isn't strictly based on numbers.  In fact I'd say that as long as multiple builds are available PvP won't work because one will always have an advantage over the other, unless the distiction is trivial. The only reason I think Blizzard even bothered is to cater to it's previous fanbase but SOE had the right idea with EQ2 in no supporting it imo. It's just not possible to make the game fair and diverse at the same time.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />When a government has ceased to protect the lives, liberty and property of the people, from whom its legitimate powers are derived, and for the advancement of whose happiness it was instituted, and so far from being a guarantee for the enjoyment of those inestimable and inalienable rights, becomes an instrument in the hands of evil rulers for their oppression. - Declaration of Independence of the State of Texas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
