                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am not a Blizzard fan because I never cared for Diablo, but many of my rl friends are.  Blizzard does have a good reputation, but I think running an MMORPG is an acid test.  I'm bothered by the downtime this week that seemed incessant, and wonder if they have the ability to pull off running a MMORPG consistently.  Time will tell.
<br />

<br />
So far I haven't seen Blizzard pulling some of the stunts that seem downright deceptive like making a mission obtainable by 3 people while it's tuned for 6 people.  Or canceling a summit knowing players will be asking what the role of their class is in this summit, then turning around and ask the players to send input in on what their class is.
<br />

<br />
Hope it does not come to that one day.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
