                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the majority of the problems being experienced to date are related to Blizzard not realizing the scale of success they would achieve at launch.  WoW blew past most of the subscriber expectations of thier management very early on and they have been playing catch up ever since.  The addition of new servers and greater bandwidth pipes into those servers almost certainly has eaten into the manhours that they would probably have been using to get content patch and fixes of game mechanics into place.  This is going to continue to be a catch up game for awhile yet.  I don't believe Blizzard is experiencing problems from any lack of desire to move forward or willingness to work, I think they are simply in a sprint trying to keep up with the monster numbers of subscribers they didn't wholly expect.  My general feeling about the state of the new games is that SOE may very well have overinvested or came close to hitting the mark with investing in EQ2 but Blizzard underinvested relative to the success they achieved.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
