                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Its nearly four months after release, and weve seen no Battlegrounds. No content patch. Server stability is still horrid (sorry, it is). The popularity of the game is an excuse I can only hear so much of. Yes, WoW is popular. Blizzard should also have anticipated this, and as said already, four months shouldve been plenty of time to weed out stability issues. The longer the queues, the crashes, the lag, and the raid bugs continue it will deter people from buying (or continuing their account). Even people like myself who are playing on low population servers are starting to feel the drag of these issues because Blizzard cant pull their head outta their ass. 
<br />

<br />
The PvP in WoW is utterly broken; there is NO reward for killing someone, be it on a PvE or pure-PvP server. As my friend Seretogis said, 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">you beat someone in PvP and you actually lose. Why? You cant tell when their going to rez up behind you and gank you when youre on a mob, or out of mana, etc. So, by winning PvP you put yourself at the mercy of the person you just killed, unless you really want to do nothing but wait for them to rez. It makes no sense.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I agree 110%
<br />

<br />
PvP is balanced in WoW because each class has a fighting chance. However what I dislike is that nearly four months after release, there is no reward system for PvP. Theres no penalty for dying either. The rez timer isnt enough to deter people anymore. At least I enjoyed the EQ PvP system; sure the classes werent all balanced to stand toe to toe, but there were obvious checks & balances in place to prevent grief, and ensure victory. Right now, PvP is who has the bigger numbers. Thats not why I picked up WoW, and the main reason I avoid putting myself in PvP situations nowadays.
<br />

<br />
As for content, Im not complaining - yet - about lack of things to do. I suppose once I run out of quests Ill moan. What I AM concerned with, is progression from 1-60 being able to be done solo, and BOOM at 60 Im forced to raid / group to complete ALL objectives for my quests. Im at level 54 now and already seeing this shift as my quest log fills up with Elite missions. Also, I have no desire to save up for a 1000g mount, so that leaves Scholomance, Strathohlm, and BRD / BRS etc to raid. Theres no Hero classes implemented yet, and I doubt for a few more months.
<br />

<br />
WoW has its perks, but this content patch needs to address a whole lotta issues and is going to set the tone for whether or not players will invest in continuing to play the game.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
