                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">re: PvP
<br />

<br />
I remember reading the boards back in ST2 and the reps swearing up and down that the next patch would include a PvP reward system.  This is entirely seperate from battlegrounds. and yet seems to have taken a back seat.  It wouldn't surprise me that BG are being prioritized over PvP rewards, even though it's obvious the level of effort required to release the former is several levels of magnitude greater.
<br />

<br />
Think about it the complexity of BG.  You need a point/reward system, in addition to the new zone, server upgrades/additions just to run them in non-slideshow form.  For PvP rewards, you need a system and a few NPCs in one place to hand the rewards out.  Vastly more simple, yet it seems to have slipped into the background.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
