                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Disclaimer:</span> This is merely my 2 coppers. Please take that for what it is worth   <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
While Wow does have its bugs, most of them are documented and are slowly being fixed.
<br />
And given the fact that this is Blizzards first MMO, I think they are doing a stellar job overall.
<br />
Look back at EQ, they STILL have bugs in the old world which they havent bothered to fix. Even further back to UO, they couldnt keep the servers going to pop mobs.... You would wander zones for HOURS and not see a single mob pop, and this lasted for months.
<br />
While I do think they jumped the gun on a few things, overall, after experiencing other MMO releases, I think they are moving with some damn fine efficiency and speed. And they are thinking out their responses, instead of just jumping on something and half  <img src="images/smiles/icon_butt.gif" alt="icon_butt.gif" border="0" />  a fix, which then leads to another fix, ad infintum.
<br />
As for PvP, you aint gonna make people happy. Look at UO for PvP. They did add honor, which fixed nothing for most people and the others simply didn't care. 
<br />
As for hacks, lets look at the sheer number of dupe bugs that were/are floating around in EQ and others. there will never be a totally hack free game out. At least Blizzard is trying to address the issues as they become aware of them and ban accounts rather than other games, which just shrug their shoulders and let it ride. 
<br />
Is it perfect? No... 
<br />
IMHO, Is it one of the funnest MMO's I have played? Yes, I think it is a fine game for the casual player.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247107" target="_blank" class="postlink">Goloth</a>
