                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Basically, i think WoW atm is a great foundation for a MMORPG. It has the potential to be  another EQ in terms of sucess.
<br />

<br />
Battlegrounds, and a PvP system that means something is needed.
<br />
More content will always be wanted, always.
<br />

<br />
When looking back to EQ, i remember what the orignal game was like, there was complaints then about certiain things, but, comming from someone who  has played wow from day 1, and EQ from day 1. Wow has the better game, which is to be expected considering its 5years made later.
<br />

<br />
But my point is, WoW have made a MMORPG, they have started well. What people want now is more content added. Be it more zones, pvp system,  or whatever.
<br />

<br />
I  think we are looking at some content in a month or so, with the idea of 3 contents a year. That isn't that bad considering its new zones etc for free.
<br />

<br />
I fullly expect an expansion in 6-9months aswell.
<br />

<br />

<br />
But, each time some content comes out i also just knopw withing 2weeks people will start asking for more content, the powergamer(which i was in EQ) will get through the content faster than Blizzard can put it out.
<br />

<br />
I really think, its just best to wait, be calm, and if needs be, retire the account for a month or two, come back after each content patch and replay then. Instead of sitting in the game with the complete lvl 60 charecter wonderining what to do.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
The above is just the opinion of a Englishman who likes beans.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
